data.enText: to learn about sth or teach sb about sth, so that you/they start to understand it

data.chText: 你需要时间熟悉我们的程序。
data.enText: You'll need time to familiarize yourself with our procedures.

example: you should acquaint yourself with your new computer
We familiarized ourselves with the new surroundings

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 familiarise

value.def: If you familiarize yourself with something, or if someone familiarizes you with it, you learn about it and start to understand it.

example.ex: I was expected to familiarise myself with the keyboard...
example.tran: 对我的要求是熟悉键盘。

example.ex: The goal of the experiment was to familiarize the people with the new laws.
example.tran: 试行的目的就是要让人们熟悉新法规。
